This paper focuses on feature selection algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining. The paper discusses the Relief-based algorithms (RBAs), which are a family of filter-style feature selection algorithms. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
